-- Metropolitan's John Melville Quits Before Merger With Momentum, Fin24 Says
-- B y   V e r n o n   W e s s e l s
-- 2010-10-06T05:50:03Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-06/metropolitan-s-john-melville-quits-before-merger-with-momentum-fin24-says.html
John Melville, the chief executive
officer of Metropolitan Holdings Ltd.’s employee benefits unit,
quit before the merger with FirstRand Ltd.’s Momentum Group,
Fin24 said.  Melville quit to join Santam Ltd., the Johannesburg-based
Internet news service said, citing Santam CEO Ian Kirk. Jannie
Venter, head of marketing and development at Metropolitan, has
also left the company, Fin24 reported.  Metropolitan and Momentum declined to comment on the
resignations, Fin24 said.   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Vernon Wessels at 
 vwessels@bloomberg.net  